Description of larva and tritonymph. Larva oval in dorsal aspect (
Fig. 12
), body light-brown, with slightly darker legs. Seta ro rather long, setae le and in shorter; pair ro inserted closest, pair in widest; all setae slightly curved and barbed; seta ex almost as long as in , but thin and smooth. Bothridium rounded, sensillus rather short, clavate, with barbed head.

